description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time opportunities available 6 month and 12 month contracts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Nursing benefited from substantial service redesign in 2012 and now includes a Rapid Response that has been integrated into the current Community Nursing Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff rotate into the Rapid Response Service /unplanned work on a daily basis but work within the core Community Nursing team with the Community Sister who has responsibility for a defined caseload of patients. Working in the Rapid Response Service will enable you to contribute to the admission avoidance agenda by supporting patients with a range of complex health and social needs to remain at home through a period of illness/crisis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Services has strong and active links with GP practices, Intermediate Care Services, Community Hospitals, acute NHS Trusts and health and social care and is committed to the delivery of high quality patient focused care using evidence-based practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit dynamic and enthusiastic individuals who have the vision to contribute to the development of new services. You will need to be highly motivated and forward thinking and possess the ability to work independently as well as within a locality team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before applying please ensure you meet the essential criteria for this position. The posts are based within identified localities however the post holders may be expected to work across the Middlesbrough, Redcar and Cleveland locality depending on service need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Core working hours for the Community Nursing Service is 8am-11pm 7 days a week, which includes the Rapid Response Service, with flexible working patterns to allow you to balance your work and family life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ann-Marie Thomas (Clinical Lead) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: ann-marie.thomas@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 944649&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
